replies.bodyText:
Agree that would be better, and it's what I originally expected hence the bug. It's a 3p library we don't control though.
Avoiding repetition of the value is a good argument for switching the approach, though I still don't love the side-effect tacked onto the end of the expression with the ifPresent approach. Perhaps something like this instead:
projects.addAll(CollectionUtils.emptyIfNull(resp.getProjects()));

or
projects.addAll(Optional.ofNullable(resp.getProjects()).orElse(Collections.emptyList()));
